<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'>I know you guys are busy. Any attention to my
questions will be mostly appreciated.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'>Is there a FAQ for mtt? May be some of my Q have
been answered before.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'>I intend to run mtt and test some performance over
Infiniband. My setup is a 2-Dell uni-core machines (i.e.: sw160,sw170) running
SLES10.0. Each host has an Infiniband HCA Card installed. Each HCA Card has 2
Physical ports which are assigned unique IP&#8217;s (i.e.: 11.4.3.160,12.4.3.160
and 11.4.3.170,12.4.3.170 respectively)<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'>Ports are connected back-to-back (port1 &lt;-&gt;
port1 and port2 &lt;-&gt; port2)<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><font size=2 face="Courier New"><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Q #1: Can I override INI file value for hostlist in command
line? If yes, please provide example.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Q #2: In your opinion, what should I specify to hostlist in
order to run mpi jobs over my Infiniband fabric? <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><font size=2 face=Arial><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Is it hostlist = sw160 sw170 <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><font size=2 face=Arial><span
style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Is it hostlist = 11.4.3.160 12.4.3.160
11.4.3.170 12.4.3.170<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Q #3: How do I determine which Interfaces mpi uses? <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Q #4: How can I determine max num of processes for my setup?
In the case of hostlist = sw160 sw170 , mtt will evaluate max_np to 2.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>In the case of hostlist = 11.4.3.160 12.4.3.160 11.4.3.170 12.4.3.170
, max_np will result to 4.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

